### The Real Problem with Borrowed Playbooks

The consulting firm that lost their best advisors? They deployed AI to handle data analysis.

Reasonable on paper.

But their best client advisors weren't valuable because they could analyze data. They were valuable because they knew *which* data mattered. Because they had relationships that surfaced information competitors couldn't access. Because they could walk into a boardroom and read the politics.

The AI didn't amplify any of that.

The AI replaced the *entry point* to it—the junior work that taught advisors how to develop judgment. The repetitive exposure that built pattern recognition over years.

So the senior advisors looked around and realized: "This company is optimizing me out of existence. They just don't know it yet."

And they left before it happened.

